        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n1. For jetty, jetty 9.4.11.v20180605 should already include the fix for CVE-2018-12538 [1]. Not sure why sonar still reports this vulnerability.\n2. For h2database, it was discovered recently in its latest version [2], so no resolution for now. Let's get it monitored. BTW, it is a test scope only dependency.\n\n[1] https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=536018\n[2] http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2018-14335",
